cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.PL 

Reasoning: 

- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a mechanism for improving TLS security in web browsers. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses the implementation of a Firefox browser extension as a proof-of-concept. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper deals with HTTPS requests and TLS configurations. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) could be relevant as the proposed mechanism could potentially impact the security of social networks and other information networks. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the implementation of the proposed mechanism as a browser extension.
